
[1]mortuary

   MOR'TUARY, n.

   1. A sort of ecclesiastical heriot, a customary gift claimed by and due
   to the minister of a parish on the death of a parishioner. It seems to
   have been originally a voluntary bequest or donation, intended to make
   amends for any failure in the payment of tithes of which the deceased
   had been guilty.

   2. A burial place.

             MOR'TUARY, a. Belonging to the burial of the dead.
